TopicTitle: [1.4] StageRecovery - Recover Funds+ from Dropped Stages - v1.8.0 (March 11, 2018)

Articles.Content:
6 minutes ago, Loren Pechtel said:

Strange--I did exactly that.  I see no sign of it  other than a message during load reporting that it's for 1.2.  I had chutes on my booster, it went splat.

How soon after launch did you jettison your booster? SR doesn't kick in until the game tries to delete the debris, but ever since 1.0 or so the game will keep objects loaded for a long time while in the atmosphere. If your booster was jettisoned fairly early in your launch, it's possible that your booster hit the ground before you got far enough away from it for the game to try to remove it (and SR to "recover" it).

If this IS what's happening, the fix is to make sure your parachutes stage when your booster separates, but set the pressure to something above 0.5 atmospheres so that they don't deploy immediately.

Edit:  An examination of the Stage Recovery mod showed it was 1.2.0 only.  As an experiment I made it say it works for 1.2.1 also--and while I'm doing so the 1.2.2 update arrived so it still doesn't match.  Still no icon.  I think I'm going to wait a few days on the game for the mods to update, though.

It's definitely possible. If RO uses a different module than stock does internally then it won't recognize it at all. It should recognize different materials though. The DR velocity definitely has to be tweaked for RO though, since 2000 is way too low. Keep in mind that there's no drag on the part when out of physics range but still above the cutoff altitude for automatic destruction, which is the only time SR activates. Ie, there's a lot of extra velocity that shouldn't actually be considered.

i noticed the "burning up" already couple times even if the stage shouldn't at all (enough parachutes , low flight profile etc).

What i could see so far this happens if you time warp too early, f.e. after circulation you drop the stage with retro rockets (to slow it down enough for re-entry) and then time warp. Stage burns up. But if you wait some time for the stage to get deep enough into the atmosphere again the stage will be recovered.

Drops from high altitude at a low angle are the worst for burning up since it will be going really fast when it hits 25km altitude without any drag applied. It's velocity at destruction, which you can watch by hovering over the vessel as it falls in map mode.

Am I doing powered recovery wrong? I am using ven stock revamp to build my rocket. I do everything that the power recovery on the first point said, I have a probe core, have 400 delta V when I decouple, twr is over 1.5+ in atmosphere, and the engine is still activated when I decouple. Do I have to mannually switch to my booster and land it myself? Here an imgur album of my craft and when I press decouple. http://imgur.com/a/QeHPj

Edit: I got it to work when I did a seperate craft and test decoupling at around 60k. It seem like powered recovery only worked when out of physics range.

95% of the things StageRecovery does only happen after a vessel has 1) left physics range and 2) gotten low enough in the atmosphere that KSP deletes it. If those two criteria aren't met, then there's a really good chance SR won't act on it. For stock KSP, physics range is 22.5km from the active vessel and the atmosphere cutoff is about 25km. Also, make sure you've got enough fuel in reserves (it can be locked if you keep a small tank for it) for powered recovery, but it sounds like you've got that covered.
Thank you for your reply. You seem like a very good mod author as you reply to every question and explain it very well

Btw, thanks for the mod, I like the extra strategy it requires.
Is  radial drogue chute not being calculated in the stage recovery helper?

@magico13 After having the crew of a few missions disappear. I managed to track down the cause to StageRecovery(using V1.6.5) and can repro it easily.
  Send a crewed ship to either the Mun or Minmus. Then setup a sub-orbital flight with Kerbin that has a SOI change. Which typically happens to me when doing a course correction when matching planes with Minmus.
  Then switch to another vessel and then switch back. The crew should then be deleted and marked as dead/missing in the astronaut complex and in the sfs file.

  I don't receive any notification of their death, but I do lose rep. Other than that this is a great mod.
